      "comment": "TARRANT COUNTY (2) fifteen-start Maiden who finds an easier contest on the quick back-up. Chipped away late with a handy fifth over 1280m at Muswellbrook. This looks much easier on a drying surface. REDALUCA GIRL (8) showed plenty of grit from the wide gate when she stuck on well to finish a close-up fourth over 1400m at Tamworth. Maps well today and will take catching. IMMORTAL ROSE (6) ticks a few boxes here with the claim after tiring late to finish sixth over 1400m at Tamworth in a Super Maiden. Drawn to get the gun run and can give this a mighty shake. DON'T SAY DO (5) stretches out to this trip for the first time after she found the 1100m too short when fourth at Scone. No excuses today.",
